### 1. Create a new task
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn FastAPI",
  "description": "Complete the task management API"
}

### 2. Update the task (use the ID from response above)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8000/tasks/one_task/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn FastAPI - Completed!",
  "description": "I have successfully learned FastAPI",
  "completed": true
}

### 3. Get all tasks to see the update
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/tasks

### 4. Get specific task
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/tasks/1

### 5. Try to update non-existent task (should give 404)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8000/tasks/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This should fail",
  "description": "Task not found"
}

### 6. Delete task (if you have delete endpoint)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/tasks/1